narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: A first-hand understanding of Gamelan  something I hadn't heard of before this course

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: first-hand learning experience, community, Phil's dedication and kindness, beautiful music that most Americans wouldn't otherwise get to learn about. No weaknesses

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Absolutely! If you get the chance to take this course, take it! It's been one of my favorites. You learn so much, but in a completely different way that you usually do at Yale. Gamelan is beautiful and unique, and while learning how to play definitely challenges you, it's unbelievably rewarding. Phil is also so supportive, and the community you form with your classmates is unlike any other. 10/10!
